20 historiated main and medium initials on f. 1ra3-8 (Hirðskrá; King with sword), f. 24ra2-5 (Bréf Magnúss konungs (Bylov); King blessing), f. 24ra2-5 (Þingfararbolkr (Bylov); Hand blessing), f. 44va11-13 (Réttarbót Magnúss Eiríkssonar 9.3.1295; King blessing; Medium initial), f. 52ra2-6 (Kristinréttr yngri [G], ch. 1; Head of Christ), f. 61va4-9 (Bréf Magnúss konungs; King and Queen), f. 62va12-15 (Þingfararbolkr; Head of Christ), f. 66ra4-8 (Kristindómsbolkr; Christ in Majesty), f. 70ra16-21 (Landavarnarbolkr; Knight armed), f. 76ra1-6 (Mannhelgisbolkr; 2 figures arguing), f. 86ra1-6 (Erfðatal, Kvennagiftingar; 2 figures swearing), f. 88va18-23 (Erfðatal; 1 figure above, 3 figures below swearing), f. 94vb6-10 (Landabrigðabolkr, Ódalsskiptum; 2 figures swearing), f. 96va9-13 (Landabrigðabolkr, Landsleigu ok varnar; 1 figure swearing), f. 99rb7-11 (Landsleigubolkr; 2 human heads above, 1 gryllus figure below), f. 118rb3-8 (Kaupabolkr; 2 figures swearing), f. 125rb17-21 (Þjófabolkr; 1 hanged figure), f. 128rb6-9 (Réttarbót Hákonar Hákonarsonar in Landslog; King blessing; Medium initial), f. 128vb10-13 (Réttarbót Magnúsar Hákonarsonar in Landslog; Head of King; Medium initial), f. 130rb2-5 (Réttarbót Eiríks Magnússonar 1280; Head of King; Medium initial), f. 132va16-20 (Réttarbót Hákonar Magnússonar 28.6.1298; 2 rams; Medium initial). In addition, three unhistoriated ornamented medium initials are found on f. 26va5-10, f. 32va22-25 and f. 38rb1-5. Finally, on ff. 140-141, historiated scenes accompany the featured calendarium in the lower margins (Hunting with falcon for May, pulling weeds for June, ploughing for July, harvesting grain for August, harvesting fruits for Septemb er, sowing for Octover, butchering for November and brewing for December). Many of the minor and remaining medium initials are inhabited and feature human heads likely connected in one way or another to the introduced text sections.
